ip banners to your website, and thoroughly test your App Clips through TestFlight.","type":"text"}],"title":"Configure and link your App Clips"},"https://github.com/Blackjacx":{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Blackjacx","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}],"title":"GitHub","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Blackjacx","type":"link"},"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/794372?v=4":{"identifier":"https:\/\/avatars.githubusercontent.com\/u\/794372?v=4","alt":"Profile image of Stefan Herold","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"https:\/\/avatars.githubusercontent.com\/u\/794372?v=4"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-719-Whats-New-in-File-Management-and-Quick-Look":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-719-Whats-New-in-File-Management-and-Quick-Look","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Your iOS app can now access files stored on external devices via USB and SMB. Understand best practices for creating a document-based app that reads, writes, and manages files on physical media or networked storage. Learn about enhancements to Quick Look on iOS and macOS that help you access and display file thumbnails."}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-719-whats-new-in-file-management-and-quick-look","title":"What’s New in File Management and Quick Look"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-247-Whats-New-in-ClassKit":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-247-Whats-New-in-ClassKit","role":"sampleCode","title":"What’s New in ClassKit","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"The ClassKit framework helps you surface your app’s valuable educational content for inclusion in a teacher’s classroom curriculum. Get an overview of the ClassKit integration workflow, debugging instructor and student roles with the Schoolwork app, and new features designed to make publishing to ClassKit easier than ever.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-247-whats-new-in-classkit"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png"}]},"https://x.com/blackjacxxx":{"identifier":"https:\/\/x.com\/blackjacxxx","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"X\/Twitter"}],"title":"X\/Twitter","url":"https:\/\/x.com\/blackjacxxx","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-510-Whats-New-in-AVAudioEngine":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-510-Whats-New-in-AVAudioEngine","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AVAudioEngine enables the realtime capture, processing, and playback of audio. Learn how to take advantage of enhancements to this powerful API, such as support for voice processing and spatial rendering mode selection, in your own audio app."}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-510-whats-new-in-avaudioengine","title":"What’s New in AVAudioEngine"},"https://wwdcnotes.github.io/WWDCNotes/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.github.io\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributions are welcome!"}],"title":"Contributions are welcome!","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.github.io\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link"},"https://www.stefan-herold.net":{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.stefan-herold.net","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"title":"Blog","url":"https:\/\/www.stefan-herold.net","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-516-Whats-New-in-Authentication":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-516-Whats-New-in-Authentication","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Secure sign-in and authentication is a key feature of a secure account-based app design. Learn how you can improve your app’s login experiences through an overview of the available authentications services and details on specific technologies such as Sign In with Apple ID, Password AutoFill for iPad Apps for Mac, advances in OAuth and WebAuthentication, and a new API for streamlined password sign-in."}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-516-whats-new-in-authentication","title":"What’s New in Authentication"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc19/717":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc19\/717","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc19\/717","checksum":null,"type":"download"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-720-Whats-New-in-Safari-Extensions":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-720-Whats-New-in-Safari-Extensions","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Safari Extensions surface your app’s unique capabilities within Safari. Discover how the latest features such as content blocking notifications and user interface management and control innovations for pages, tabs, and popovers make your Safari App Extensions and Content Blockers even more powerful. Learn about the latest APIs and best practices for communicating between your extension and your app.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"What’s New in Safari Extensions","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-720-whats-new-in-safari-extensions"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","kind":"symbol","title":"WWDC Notes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19":{"title":"WWDC19","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 11, Swift 5.1, iOS 12, macOS 10.15, tvOS 13, watchOS 6."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"code":"Combine","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Core Haptics","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Create ML","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-515-Whats-New-in-Safari":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-515-Whats-New-in-Safari","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The latest version of Safari on macOS and iOS is packed with new capabilities that both web developers and their customers will love. Discover how to take advantage of new features including powerful new Safari Extensions APIs for window, tab, and popover management, content blocking notifications, and enhancements to make link following in your Mac apps and iPad Apps for Mac a great experience.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"What’s New in Safari","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-515-whats-new-in-safari"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/Blackjacx":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/blackjacx","title":"Stefan Herold (16 notes)","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/Blackjacx","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS Engineer a.d. 2009 • iOS \/ OSX Enthusiast • WWDC19 • Past: flinc, Deutsche Telekom, NOLTE&LAUTH • Passionate Mountainbiker"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10098-Whats-new-in-Universal-Links":{"role":"sampleCode","title":"What’s new in Universal Links","type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10098-Whats-new-in-Universal-Links","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10098-whats-new-in-universal-links","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Universal Links help people access your content, whether or not they have your app installed. Get the details on the latest updates for the Universal Links API, including support for Apple Watch and SwiftUI. Learn how you can reduce the size and complexity of your app-site-association file with enhanced pattern matching features like wildcards, substitution variables, and Unicode support. And discover how cached associated domains data will improve the initial launch experience for people using your app."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-808-Whats-New-in-iOS-Design":{"title":"What’s New in iOS Design","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-808-Whats-New-in-iOS-Design","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-808-whats-new-in-ios-design","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover how to update your app’s interface for Dark Mode to create beautiful and accessible apps. And learn how refinements to modal sheets and the new contextual menu UI can help improve usability and lead to more powerful and efficient workflows."}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article"}}}